# Medium API Publishing Guide

## Summary

After researching similar cases online, I found that **Medium's API still works** despite being officially deprecated. This completely bypasses browser automation issues.

## The Problem

Browser automation on Medium fails because:
1. **Anti-bot detection** - Medium detects automated interactions in contenteditable fields
2. **React state management** - Complex editor requires specific event sequences
3. **"Something is wrong" error** - Common when automation is detected

## The Solution: Use Medium API

Medium's REST API is "deprecated" but **still fully functional** for posting articles.

### Step 1: Get Your Integration Token

1. Go to https://medium.com/me/settings
2. Scroll to "Integration tokens" section
3. Enter a description: "OpenTwins Agent"
4. Click "Get token"
5. Copy the token (it looks like: `2dbc7c2b4e74c3b58e8d24b1f3a6e9c8d7b6a5c4`)

⚠️ **Important**: Store this securely. It never expires (unless revoked).

### Step 2: Set Environment Variable

```bash
export MEDIUM_TOKEN="your_token_here"
```

Or add to your shell profile (~/.zshrc or ~/.bashrc):
```bash
echo 'export MEDIUM_TOKEN="your_token_here"' >> ~/.zshrc
source ~/.zshrc
```

### Step 3: Use One of the Scripts

#### Option A: Node.js Script (Recommended)

```bash
node /tmp/medium-api-post.js
```

#### Option B: Bash Script (Requires jq)

```bash
bash /tmp/medium-api-post.sh
```

## API Endpoint Details

### Authentication
```
GET https://api.medium.com/v1/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN
```

Returns user info including `userId` needed for posting.

### Create Post
```
POST https://api.medium.com/v1/users/{userId}/posts
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Article Title",
  "contentFormat": "markdown",  // or "html"
  "content": "# Your content here...",
  "tags": ["tag1", "tag2", "tag3"],
  "publishStatus": "public"  // or "draft", "unlisted"
}
```

### Response (201 Created)
```json
{
  "data": {
    "id": "abc123",
    "title": "Article Title",
    "authorId": "...",
    "url": "https://medium.com/@{{handle_slug}}/article-title-abc123",
    "publishStatus": "public",
    "publishedAt": 1234567890,
    "tags": ["tag1", "tag2", "tag3"]
  }
}
```

## Integration with Agent

### Update TOOLS.md to include API method:

```markdown
## Article Publishing Methods

### Method 1: API (Recommended)
- Requires: MEDIUM_TOKEN environment variable
- Pro: Reliable, fast, no browser issues
- Con: Requires one-time token setup
- Script: Use medium-api-post.js template

### Method 2: Browser (Fallback)
- Use only if API fails
- Subject to anti-bot detection
- Slower and less reliable
```

### Update schedule.json tasks:

```json
{
  "action": "publish_article",
  "config": {
    "method": "api",  // or "browser" as fallback
    "article_ref": "article-1"
  }
}
```

